2️⃣ Create S3 Bucket

Log in to AWS Console → S3 → Create Bucket

Bucket Name: must be unique, e.g., my-static-website-demo

Region: nearest to your users

Public access: Uncheck Block all public access → acknowledge warning

Click Create bucket

3️⃣ Upload Website Files

Open your bucket → Upload

Add all files from your folder:

index.html

style.css

script.js

Click Upload

Set Bucket Policy for Public Access

Go to Permissions → Bucket Policy

Paste this policy (replace YOUR_BUCKET_NAME):

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::YOUR_BUCKET_NAME/*"
    }
  ]
}


Save changes

5️⃣ Enable Static Website Hosting

Go to Properties → Static website hosting

Select Enable

Index document: index.html

Error document (optional): error.html

Save changes

You will get Website Endpoint URL, e.g.:

http://my-static-website-demo.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com
